net.bytebuddy.agent.builder

Interface AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator.Default
    Enclosing interface:
    AgentBuilder

    public static interface AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator
    A binary locator allows to specify how binary data is located by an AgentBuilder.

    • Nested Class Summary

      Nested Classes 
      Modifier and Type Interface and Description
      static class  AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator.Default
      A default implementation of a AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator that is using a TypePool.Default with a TypePool.CacheProvider.Simple and a ClassFileLocator.ForClassLoader.
      static interface  AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator.Initialized
      A AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator in initialized state.

    • Method Detail

      • initialize

        AgentBuilder.BinaryLocator.Initialized initialize(String typeName,
                                                  byte[] binaryRepresentation,
                                                  ClassLoader classLoader)
        Initializes this binary locator.
        Parameters:
        typeName - The binary name of the type that is being instrumented.
        binaryRepresentation - The binary representation of the instrumented type.
        classLoader - The class loader of the instrumented type. Might be null if this class loader represents the bootstrap class loader.
        Returns:
        This binary locator in its initialized form.
